	"keywords": "React, Express, Postgres",
	"description": "In this tutorial we&#x27;re going to build out a full stack React blog along with a\nblog admin back end. \n\nI will walk you through all the steps in detail.\n\nBy the end of this tutorial, you will have enough knowledge to build fairly\ncomplex full stack apps using modern tools: React, Express, and a PostgreSQL\ndatabase. \n\nTo keeps things concise, I will do the bare minimum styling/layout and leave\nthat up to the reader. \n\nCompleted Project:\nhttps://github.com/iqbal125/react-hooks-complete-fullstack\n\nAd",
	"headline": "Full Stack React: How to Build Your Own Blog Using Express, Hooks, &amp; Postgres.",
